title: Led Zeppelin - 1970.09.04 Inglewood, LA (Vinyl Version)
description:
Led Zeppelin - 1970.09.04 Inglewood, LA (Vinyl Version)   
(another source of the "Blueberry Hill" show, arguably the best 
sounding version but also incomplete)

Led Zeppelin - 1970.09.04 
Venue: The Forum 
City: Inglewood, Los Angeles 
Country: USA 
Title: "Led Zeppelin Live at the Los Angeles Forum 9-4-70" LP
Label: Rubber Dubber
Quality: Excellent stereo audience recording

Info:
Rubber Dubber version / stereo audience recording (vinyl source only in circulation): Live At The Los Angeles Forum 9-4-70, Rubber Dubber 70-007-01A/02B/03C /04D (TCD-30) 

Tracklist:
1.Bring It On Home
2.That's The Way
3.Bron-Yr-Aur
4.Since I've Been Loving You
5.Organ Solo
6.Thank You
7.What Is and What Should Never Be
8.Whole Lotta Love medley
9.Communication Breakdown medley

This is how the tracks are laid out on the LP:
Side one:
 Bring It On Home
 That's The Way
Side two:
 Bron-Yr-Aur
 Since I've Been Loving You
 Organ solo
Side three:
 Thank You
 What Is and What Should Never Be
 Whole Lotta Love + medley
Side four:
 Whole Lotta Love + medley (cont.)
 Communication Breakdown + medley
